-- UBS Hires Matus From Bank of America as a Senior U.S. Economist, Memo Says
-- Jeff Kearns
-- 2010-04-23T14:09:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-23/ubs-hires-matus-from-bank-of-america-as-a-senior-u-s-economist-memo-says.html

          
          
             UBS AG hired Drew Matus, who worked
at Bank of America Corp. and the Federal Reserve Bank of New
York, as a senior U.S. economist and managing director,
according to an internal memo today.  
 UBS spokeswoman Allison Chin-Leong confirmed the 
appointment. Matus will be based in Stamford, Connecticut, and
report to Maury Harris, the chief U.S. economist at the firm,
according to the memo.  
